Reasoning: 
1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - This paper deals with sentiment and subjectivity analysis in online videos, which falls under the domain of natural language processing. 
2. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper focuses on analyzing videos, which is a multimedia content. 
3. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper also deals with per-frame visual features, which is related to computer vision. 
4. cs.SD (Sound) - The paper also deals with per-millisecond annotated audio features, which is related to sound processing. 
5. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - The paper discusses the lack of a proper dataset and methodology, which is related to information retrieval.
